HEADWORD: Excursus
<hw>Ex*cur"sus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr.
<ets>excurrere</ets>, <ets>excursum</ets>. See
<er>Excurrent</er>.]</ety> <def>A dissertation or digression appended to
a work, and containing a more extended exposition of some important
point or topic.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Excusable</ent>⟦br⟧
